fusionIoDimmInfoState.name: fusionIoDimmInfoState
fusionIoDimmInfoState.description: The current state of the attached client device. In order to function normally, the device must be in the 'attached' state. Quiescent states: attached = device is ready for normal use detached = device is stopped minimal = driver loaded but firmware needs updating error = device is not working properly Transitional states: attaching = device is initializing scanning = part of device initialization detaching = device is stopping formatting = the format operation is in process updating = the firmware is being updated Operations: attach = make device operational detach = take device off-line format = re-formats device update = firmware update Device state must be minimal or detached to update the firmware and must be detached in order format.

fusionIoDimmInfoClientDeviceName.name: fusionIoDimmInfoClientDeviceName
fusionIoDimmInfoClientDeviceName.description: The name of the attached client device.

fusionIoDimmInfoPCIAddress.name: fusionIoDimmInfoPCIAddress
fusionIoDimmInfoPCIAddress.description: Device address on the PCI bus.

fusionIoDimmInfoLongTermWearoutDate.name: fusionIoDimmInfoLongTermWearoutDate
fusionIoDimmInfoLongTermWearoutDate.description: The date that the drive is estimated to reach the wearout threshold based on drive usage in the long-term interval.

fusionIoDimmInfoShortTermNonWritableDate.name: fusionIoDimmInfoShortTermNonWritableDate
fusionIoDimmInfoShortTermNonWritableDate.description: The date that the drive is estimated to go non-writable based on drive usage in the short-term interval.

fusionIoDimmInfoLongTermNonWritableDate.name: fusionIoDimmInfoLongTermNonWritableDate
fusionIoDimmInfoLongTermNonWritableDate.description: The date that the drive is estimated to go non-writable based on drive usage in the long-term interval.

fusionIoDimmInfoReducedWriteReason.description: Reason card is in reduced write mode.

fusionIoDimmInfoMilliVoltsMin.description: Minimum voltage level of PCIe 12 volt bus in millivolts. A value of 0 means value could not be determined.

fusionIoDimmInfoMilliWatts.description: Current wattage drawn on the PCIe 12 volt bus in milliwatts. A value of 0 means value could not be determined.

fusionIoDimmInfoMilliWattsPeak.name: fusionIoDimmInfoMilliWattsPeak
fusionIoDimmInfoMilliWattsPeak.description: Peak wattage drawn on the PCIe 12 volt bus in milliwatts. A value of 0 means value could not be determined.

fusionIoDimmInfoMilliAmps.description: Amperage flowing on the PCIe 12 volt bus in milliamps. A value of 0 means value could not be determined.

fusionIoDimmInfoMilliAmpsPeak.description: Peak amperage flowing on the PCIe 12 volt bus in milliamps. A value of 0 means value could not be determined.

fusionIoDimmInfoPowerlossProtectDisabled.description: A true condition indicates that powerloss protection is available but disabled.

fusionIoDimmInfoInternalTempHigh.description: A true condition indicates that the internal temperature is nearing the maximum rating.

fusionIoDimmInfoAmbientTemp.description: The current ambient temperature of the device in Celsius.

fusionIoDimmInfoPCIPowerCompatibility.name: fusionIoDimmInfoPCIPowerCompatibility
fusionIoDimmInfoPCIPowerCompatibility.description: The power compatibility of the PCI-E slot. If the value is not optimal, the status and condition variables will be set accordingly.

fusionIoDimmInfoActualGoverningLevel.name: fusionIoDimmInfoActualGoverningLevel
fusionIoDimmInfoActualGoverningLevel.description: The level of governing currently happening on the device. This may be due to any of several reasons. Current reasons are because of high temperature, power shortage, or to prolong life of the drive. none = no governing active light = light governing moderate = moderate governing heavy = heavy governing unavailable = governing level unavailable

fusionIoDimmInfoLifespanGoverningLevel.name: fusionIoDimmInfoLifespanGoverningLevel
fusionIoDimmInfoLifespanGoverningLevel.description: Governing may be impacted for the sake of prolonging longevity of the device. This value indicates the level of contribution for longevity. none = no governing active light = light governing moderate = moderate governing heavy = heavy governing unavailable = governing level unavailable

fusionIoDimmInfoPowerGoverningLevel.name: fusionIoDimmInfoPowerGoverningLevel
fusionIoDimmInfoPowerGoverningLevel.description: Governing may be impacted due to a lack of power available to the device. This value indicates the level of contribution due to lack of power. none = no governing active light = light governing moderate = moderate governing heavy = heavy governing unavailable = governing level unavailable

fusionIoDimmInfoThermalGoverningLevel.name: fusionIoDimmInfoThermalGoverningLevel
fusionIoDimmInfoThermalGoverningLevel.description: Governing may be impacted due to the device reaching high temperatures. This value indicates the level of contribution due to high temperatures. none = no governing active light = light governing moderate = moderate governing heavy = heavy governing unavailable = governing level unavailable

fusionIoDimmInfoLifespanGoverningEnabled.name: fusionIoDimmInfoLifespanGoverningEnabled
fusionIoDimmInfoLifespanGoverningEnabled.description: A true condition indicates that lifespan governing is enabled.

fusionIoDimmInfoInternalTempCritical.name: fusionIoDimmInfoInternalTempCritical
fusionIoDimmInfoInternalTempCritical.description: A true condition indicates that temperature is at a critical level.

fusionIoDimmInfoInternalTempShutdown.description: A true condition indicates that temperature is has surpassed a critical level and the device will shut down.

fusionIoDimmInfoPcieErrorsIndicator.name: fusionIoDimmInfoPcieErrorsIndicator
fusionIoDimmInfoPcieErrorsIndicator.description: Indicates whether correctable or uncorrectable PCIe errors have been detected on the PCIe bus.

fusionIoDimmInfoVccIntErrorIndicator.description: A true condition indicates the device is experiencing a VccInt out of range error.

fusionIoDimmInfoVccAuxErrorIndicator.name: fusionIoDimmInfoVccAuxErrorIndicator

fusionIoDimmExtnShortTermWindow.description: The number of hours in the short-term usage characterization window. If this value is non-zero, then the short-term start date will automatically track with the short-term end date by the number of hours specified.

fusionIoDimmExtnWriteRateAutoCalc.description: Set this true to automatically calculate the long-term and short-term average write rate based on the start and end dates selected. Otherwise, the average write rate must be set manually.

fusionIoDimmExtnLongTermAvgU.name: fusionIoDimmExtnLongTermAvgU
fusionIoDimmExtnLongTermAvgU.description: The upper word of the long-term average write rate used to characterize drive usage. This will be automatically calculated based on long-term start and end dates if the auto calc value is true.

fusionIoDimmExtnLongTermAvgL.name: fusionIoDimmExtnLongTermAvgL

fusionIoDimmExtnConfidenceInterval.description: This defines the confidence interval used to calculate the wearout and non-writable dates. Expressed as a percentage, this value reflects the confidence in the short and long-term averages used to characterize drive usage.

fusionIoDimmTrapFlags.name: fusionIoDimmTrapFlags
fusionIoDimmTrapFlags.description: This is a collection of flags used only during trap delivery. Each bit has the following meaning: Bit 5-31: Reserved (always 0) Bit 2-4: Trap Condition 0 = Not used (for backward compatibility) 1 = Condition unknown or N/A 2 = Condition ok 3 = Condition degraded 4 = Condition failed Bit 1: Reserved (always zero) Bit 0: Reserved (always zero) NOTE: bit 31 is the most significant bit, bit 0 is the least significant.
